<%#
  Shared shell for a pet's profile tabs (About, Edit, and future tabs).

  Layout: a horizontal header bar (avatar + name on the left, the tab nav, and
  the "+ Record" action on the right, with a divider beneath) sits ABOVE the
  tab's content, which spans the full width below it.

  Every tab renders through here, so they all share identical structure and
  can't drift apart.

  Locals:
    pet              - the Pet record
    active_tab       - which tab is current (:about, :edit, …)
    content_partial  - partial to render below the header (e.g. "pets/about")
%>
<%= turbo_frame_tag "pet_content", class: "d-block", data: { turbo_action: "advance" } do %>
  <%= render "pets/profile_header", pet: pet, active_tab: active_tab %>
  <%= render content_partial, pet: pet %>
<% end %>
